Subject: [PATCH AP-01b] vmnet: add OBJECT_FILES_NON_STANDARD objtool bypass (kernel >= 6.17)

vmnet's userif.c contains non-standard assembly or control flow patterns
that objtool in kernel 6.17+ flags as invalid. Mark userif.o with
OBJECT_FILES_NON_STANDARD so the kernel build excludes it from objtool
validation while keeping all other compilation checks active.

Applied by: _autopatch_objtool_vmnet() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  kernel >= 6.17 or >= 7.x  (KernelVersion.needs_objtool_patches())

---
 vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
--- a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
+++ b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
@@ -27,6 +27,10 @@ obj-m += $(DRIVER).o
 $(DRIVER)-y := driver.o hub.o userif.o netif.o bridge.o procfs.o smac_compat.o \
 	       smac.o vnetEvent.o vnetUserListener.o
 
+# Disable objtool for files using non-standard asm (kernel 6.17+)
+OBJECT_FILES_NON_STANDARD_userif.o := y
+OBJECT_FILES_NON_STANDARD := y
+
